Let's build the useItinerary custom hook. This hook will be the engine of your application, managing the state for the trip plan, handling the communication with the Gemini API, and managing loading and error states.

Overview of the Solution
The hook will perform the following actions:

State Management: Track the itinerary object, isLoading status, and any validationErrors or API error messages.


API Integration: Initialize the @google/genai client using the API key from your environment variables.

Prompt Engineering: Construct a detailed prompt for the Gemini model based on the origin, destination, and mandatoryStops provided by the user.

Response Handling: Parse the AI's response and update the UI state.

Implementation: hooks/useItinerary.ts
First, ensure you have the necessary types defined. Then, create the hook file:

TypeScript
import { useState, useCallback } from 'react';
import { GoogleGenerativeAI } from '@google/genai';
import { GEMINI_MODEL } from '../constants';
import { Itinerary, FormData } from '../types';

// Accessing the API key from your .env.local file 
const genAI = new GoogleGenerativeAI(import.meta.env.VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY || '');

export const useItinerary = () => {
  const [itinerary, setItinerary] = useState<Itinerary | null>(null);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [validationErrors, setValidationErrors] = useState<Record<string, string>>({});
  const [lastData, setLastData] = useState<FormData | null>(null);

  const handleGenerate = useCallback(async (formData: FormData, isAlt: boolean = false) => {
    setIsLoading(true);
    setError(null);
    setLastData(formData);

    try {
      const model = genAI.getGenerativeModel({ model: GEMINI_MODEL }); //

      const prompt = `
        Create a detailed road trip itinerary from ${formData.origin} to ${formData.destination}.
        Include these mandatory stops: ${formData.mandatoryStops.map(s => s.location).join(', ')}.
        Maximum driving hours per day: ${formData.maxDriveHours}.
        Travel mode: ${formData.travelMode}.
        Please return the data in a strict JSON format matching the Itinerary type.
      `;

      const result = await model.generateContent(prompt);
      const response = await result.response;
      const text = response.text();

      // Basic JSON parsing of the AI response
      const data = JSON.parse(text.replace(/```json|```/g, ''));
      setItinerary(data);
      return true;
    } catch (err) {
      console.error("Generation error:", err);
      setError("Failed to generate itinerary. Please check your API key and connection.");
      return false;
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  }, []);

  return {
    itinerary,
    isLoading,
    error,
    validationErrors,
    lastData,
    handleGenerate,
    setError
  };
};

